subSubSection.paragraph:
Cirri:
All six pairs of cirri located close to each other. Cirrus I with anterior and posterior rami similar length (26 and 28 segments, respectively); proximal segments of both rami robust (cf 

Buckeridge 
et al.
2013

), distal half of rami antenniform (
Figure 4A
); anterior and posterior rami with length ratio of ramus bearing antenniform segments to robust segments ~1:1 (
Figure 4A
). 
Paratype
with ~1:1 length ratio of antenniform to robust segments along rami of cirrus I (
Figure 6B
); setae long, serrulate on both rami (
Figure 5A, B
). Cirrus II with both rami similar length (anterior 42, posterior 41 segments); last 10 proximal segments robust, segment height 1.5 times width (
Figure 4B
); rami antenniform from half to distal region; length ratio of antenniform segments to robust segments ~1: 
1 in
both rami (
Figure 4B
); antenniform segments of cirrus II with 3 pairs of long setae and 2 pairs of short setae (
Figure 4B
).

Cirrus III with rami similar in length (both 54 segmented); setae serrulate, with very short, sparse setules (
Figure 4C
).

Trophi:
Maxilla subtriangular, exterior margin with simple setae (
Figure 5E, F
). Maxillule cutting edge slightly curved, with dense, simple setae on cutting margin; interior margin slightly convex (
Figure 5G, H
). Mandible tridentoid (
Figure 7A
); first tooth large, robust, sharp, separated from lower teeth (
Figure 7B
); second and third teeth comb-shaped, ~12 sharp spines on cutting edges (
Figure 7C, D
), cutting edges of second and third teeth short, ~1/5 total length of mandible; inferior angle blunt, with dense, sharp spines (
Figure 7E
); lower margin with simple setae (
Figure 7F
). Mandibular palp subtriangular, tip and outer margin with simple setae (
Figure 7G
). Labrum non bullate, with small, concaved notch; single array of small, sharp teeth at notch (
Figure 7H
).
